As the Minnesota Department of Education works closely with the Minnesota Department of Health to plan for the 2020-21 school year, they want to hear from families about their experience with the distance learning this spring.

This feedback is extremely valuable to them. This information will allow them to help families as you balance the responsibilities of work and family, while also supporting student learning.

http://sgiz.mobi/s3/2020-Parent-Distance-Learning-Feedback-Survey

The survey will close on June 30, 2020.

post_text: As residents of the Minneapolis/St. Paul community, we are deeply saddened by the recent events that have impacted us all. Words cannot express sufficient sorrow for those who have been most directly touched by recent misfortunes and the death of George Floyd. Every day at Beacon Academy we strive to support our students as they navigate their young lives. As an organization we want to let you know we are here to support you, to hear you and to listen to you. In addition, as a character education school we want to live by the moral traits we practice. We believe in our families, students and staff. We want you to know you can reach out to us for support.
text: As residents of the Minneapolis/St. Paul community, we are deeply saddened by the recent events that have impacted us all. Words cannot express sufficient sorrow for those who have been most directly touched by recent misfortunes and the death of George Floyd. Every day at Beacon Academy we strive to support our students as they navigate their young lives. As an organization we want to let you know we are here to support you, to hear you and to listen to you. In addition, as a character education school we want to live by the moral traits we practice. We believe in our families, students and staff. We want you to know you can reach out to us for support.

We also continue to provide meals to our families that need them; approximately 120 daily! Last week Ollie the Otter made an apprearance at meal pick up as well as a few teachers who greeted our families at a distance. Our students in childcare decorated our windows with hearts to continue to spread a message of love during this time. We miss you all and get great joy when we see your faces when you arrive for meals and packets. Stay safe and well until we can all be together again!

post_text: Today we say goodbye to Ms. Patty Blake. She has been at Beacon for four years. Patty has filled many roles in her time here at Beacon. From being a paraprofessional to long term subbing, Patty accepted every challenge with a smile on her face and a willingness in her heart. We wish her luck in her next chapter! Come back and visit anytime. You will be greatly missed!
